{Begin SubSec BIG}{FnDef {FnName NEWFONT} {FnArgs SIZE}{TextThe function {FnName NEWFONT} sets up default fonts to be "size", where size is one of the atoms {lisp HUGE}, {lisp BIG}, {lisp MEDIUM}, {lisp STANDARD} or {lisp SMALL}. It changes the prettyprint fonts, the default font for the break window, typein, Lafite, menus, etc. {FnName NEWFONT} does this by resetting {var FONTPROFILE} and then setting the fonts for all of the known windows. The font profile in the BIG package is slightly different than the "standard system" one, in that it sets font classes TEXTFONT, TEXTBOLDFONT and then uses the variable {lisp FONTVARS} to reset other fonts in terms of the ones in {lisp FONTPROFILE}.}